Ad Text:
Finance Planning & Analysis Manager - Melbourne CBD
Location: Melbourne, VIC
Company: BGIS - Major Victorian Government Services Portfolio
Employment Type: Full-Time, Permanent, Hybrid with Flexible Start/Finish times within Core Business Hours

üåø We acknowledge the Traditional Custodians of the land on which we work, and pay our respects to Elders past, present and emerging.

About BGIS
BGIS is a global leader in integrated facilities management, delivering innovative and sustainable solutions across a wide range of industries. We are committed to high standards of safety, efficiency and operational excellence, supported by a values-led, people-centred culture.

Purpose of the Role
BGIS is seeking an experienced Finance Planning & Analysis Manager to guide the financial planning, forecasting, commercial insights and portfolio-wide reporting for a newly acquired Victorian Government services contract. Reporting directly to the Contract Director, you will work collaboratively with client representatives and BGIS teams to uplift financial governance, strengthen transparency and support well-informed operational decision-making.

The ideal candidate will be thoughtful, analytical and collaborative - someone who values clarity, continuous improvement and partnership, and who brings curiosity and care to supporting high-quality financial outcomes.

Key Responsibilities

Financial Planning & Forecasting
- Deliver annual budgets, quarterly forecasts and multi-year financial modelling
- Provide forward-looking financial analysis to support risk management and portfolio strategy
- Model the financial impacts of operational changes, asset decisions and contract variations

Performance Analysis & Reporting
- Prepare monthly and quarterly financial performance reports for governance forums
- Ensure accuracy in revenue, cost, margin and accrual reporting
- Identify cost drivers, performance trends and improvement opportunities

Commercial & Contract Support
- Support pricing, scenario modelling, commercial evaluations and contract change requests
- Ensure alignment with contractual obligations and cost recovery requirements
- Collaborate with Procurement on vendor assessments and financial efficiencies

Operational Business Partnering
- Work closely with Operational Leaders to review financial performance
- Provide accessible insights for decision-making and continuous improvement

Digital & Systems Enablement
- Use Power BI, Microsoft Fabric and modelling tools to enhance reporting and financial intelligence
- Develop automated workflows in Power Automate to streamline processes and approvals

Education, Experience & Skills

Essential
- CA/CPA qualified (or equivalent)
- Significant experience in FP&A, financial leadership or commercial analysis
- Strong financial modelling skills (Excel, scenario modelling, Power BI)
- High proficiency in digital systems and data-driven reporting
- Strong communication capability, able to translate financial concepts for non-finance audiences
- Experience in FM, government, infrastructure or complex service contracts
- Commitment to innovation, workflow improvement and digital uplift

Desirable
- Exposure to FM technologies or contract-based financial frameworks
- Additional training in analytics, automation or commercial evaluation
- Experience in large public-sector or highly regulated environments

Workplace Flexibility
This position is based at our Melbourne CBD office, close to public transport.
Following onboarding and probation, the role will transition to a hybrid arrangement (2 days WFH, 3 days in the office).
The role operates within core business hours, with some flexibility to support operational needs, and may occasionally require visiting client sites within the CBD.

Why Join BGIS?

Key Benefits Include:
‚úî AFR Best Places to Work 2024 & 2025
‚úî Winner of Inspiring Workplaces Award 2025
‚úî Global organisation recognised for innovation & excellence
‚úî WORK180 Endorsed Employer & Top 5 for career development
‚úî Health and wellbeing support, EAP, flu vaccinations

BGIS is an equal opportunity employer. We strongly encourage applications from women, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, LGBTQ+ individuals and people from culturally diverse backgrounds.

Ad Text:
Our vision is simple:¬†HAPPY HEALTHY KIDS.

The Kids Research Institute Australia is one of the largest and most successful medical research institutes in Australia. We are dedicated to improving the health and lives of children everywhere through groundbreaking research. Our new¬†Research Reimagined 2025‚Äì35 Strategic Plan¬†will amplify our impact over the next decade, ensuring our discoveries make a real difference to children and their families both in our community, and around the world.

The Opportunity

Our Innovation & Impact team champions the translation of research into real-world solutions. Working collaboratively with researchers, professional services, partners and communities, the team works to scale and accelerate measurable improvements in child health and wellbeing. We are now pleased to be growing our team, as our work and impact continue to expand. ¬†

The Head of Research Consulting will play a pivotal role in the implementation of the Research Reimagined strategy. Working closely with the Director, Innovation & Impact, this role will drive the strategic expansion and impact of the Institute‚Äôs contract research and evaluation capability. You will lead the development and implementation of a research consulting strategy, and grow a high performing team, to position the Institute as a national leader in research consulting.

In this role, you will:

Develop and implement a strategy for research consulting services aligned with the Institute‚Äôs goal to deliver financially sustainable impact.

Collaborate with senior leaders to embed research consulting as a highly valued practice across research themes.

Proactively build relationships with government agencies, NGOs, industry, and other external stakeholders.

Develop a pipeline of high impact work to enable the growth and development of a high-quality team.

Conveniently based in our modern offices within Perth Children‚Äôs Hospital, this full-time role will be offered on an ongoing basis. Part-time will be considered for the right candidate.

About You

To be successful in this role, you will hold a tertiary qualification (preferably a higher degree) in a relevant discipline such as public health, psychology, or health sciences. Along with this, you will demonstrate:

Proven leadership in research consulting, evaluation, or contract research.

Strong strategic thinking and business development capability.

Experience in qualitative and quantitative research methodologies.

Ability to lead teams and manage complex projects in dynamic environments.

Experience in government procurement processes and tender compliance frameworks, including familiarity with Australian public sector contracting requirements is advantageous.

At The Kids Research Institute Australia, we are committed to building a workplace culture that¬†reflects the communities we serve. We actively recruit, support and welcome applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disability, culturally and linguistically diverse communities, LGBTQIA+ people, people of all ages, and those with diverse lived experiences. We also provide reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process and in the workplace, ensuring everyone has the opportunity to thrive.¬†¬†

If you meet many, but not all, of the role requirements, we encourage you to apply. We also welcome you to mention any career breaks in your cover letter to help us understand your journey.

Our commitment to diversity and inclusion is reflected in how we:

Support staff-led inclusion and allyship groups.

Offer flexible work practices that recognise different needs and life stages.

Provide training, development and mentoring opportunities to increase inclusive leadership and create an environment where all staff can thrive.

Partner with communities to strengthen cultural awareness and belonging.

Ensure adjustments and accessible practices are available for diverse community groups.¬†¬†

We continually strive to measure our progress and improve where we can.

Alongside our inclusive culture, you‚Äôll enjoy:¬†¬†

Extra annual leave at Christmas and Easter.

Salary packaging and entertainment benefits.

Health and wellbeing programs with weekly events.

Flexible and hybrid working options.

Recognition and professional development opportunities, including LinkedIn Learning.

Modern offices with sit-to-stand desks and end-of-trip facilities.

Staff discounts on travel, IT, stationery, and access to corporate health insurance.

How to apply

If this role feels like the right fit and an exciting new opportunity for you, please click on 'Apply Now' to visit¬†our Career Site, view the Job Description, and submit your application.

Please include a cover letter (no more than 2 pages) that specifically addresses the skills and experience outlined in the ‚ÄúAbout You‚Äù section.

Applications will only be accepted through our career portal.¬†If you are experiencing technical difficulties or require reasonable accommodations in completing your application, please contact recruitment@thekids.org.au.

For more information about the role please contact the Recruitment Team. ¬†

About Euc


We‚Äôre on a mission to make good health last a lifetime. More than 1 billion people live with obesity worldwide, driving preventable chronic conditions. We‚Äôre here to build better long-term care.

Euc is the company behind Juniper, one of the world‚Äôs largest weight-management programs combining GLP-1 medication with personalised nutrition, movement support, and clinician-led care from prescribers, nurses, health coaches, pharmacists, and dietitians. Our published clinical research shows that our combined clinical and behavioural approach helps patients lose significantly more weight during their treatment with Juniper by four times.

Our Growth Story:

130% YoY revenue growth and 90% reduction in cash burn, with $100M+ raised from investors including BOND, NewView, Blackbird and Airtree.
Scaled to over 100,000 monthly active patients across our weight-management program.
Grew the UK patient base from 4,000 to ~40,000 and received selective NICE endorsement to provide services to the NHS.
Tailored our offering to over 5,000 patients in Germany and Japan
About the role (What you‚Äôll be doing)


As the Data Science Lead at Eucalyptus, you‚Äôll lead the development and application of advanced analytics, machine learning, and AI solutions to drive strategic, commercial, and clinical outcomes. You‚Äôll partner closely with Product, Engineering and the broader Data team, to solve high-impact problems, operationalise models, and embed data processes as a core part of the product offering.

In this role, you‚Äôll balance technical leadership and hands-on delivery ‚Äî setting the vision for how data science is applied while also contributing to complex projects, from sophisticated personalised health insights, to extensive patient context management. You‚Äôll ensure the team‚Äôs work is impactful, reliable, and aligned with organisational priorities.

Lead high-impact data science projects: Own the scoping, design, and delivery of models and data context management pipelines that inform highly personalised systems in the technology roadmap.
Guide technical direction: Define the standards, methodologies, and best practices for data science at Eucalyptus, ensuring work is reproducible, explainable, and production-ready.
Collaborate cross-functionally: Partner with stakeholders across the business to translate ambiguous problems into well-defined data science projects with measurable value.
Ensure robust operationalisation: Work with Data Engineering and ML Ops to deploy models, monitor performance, and integrate outputs into products, platforms, and workflows.
Mentor and develop the team: Grow the skills and capabilities of data scientists and analysts through coaching, feedback, and technical guidance.
Stay current: Keep up with established industry practices and emerging methodologies to ensure the team‚Äôs work remains effective and relevant.
About you (Who you are)


You‚Äôre an experienced data science leader with a proven ability to deliver technically sound, commercially valuable solutions. You balance strategic thinking with hands-on technical work, and you‚Äôre skilled at influencing both technical and non-technical audiences.

7+ years of experience in data science, machine learning, or advanced analytics, with at least 2 years in a leadership role.
Proven track record of delivering models and analytics that have driven measurable business or product outcomes.
Strong technical foundation in statistical analysis, machine learning, feature engineering, and model evaluation, and context management for AI systems.
Experience in production environments, working closely with Data Engineering and ML Ops to deploy and monitor models.
Excellent communication skills with the ability to convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
Hands-on expertise in SQL, Python, and modern ML/analytics libraries; familiarity with cloud environments (preferably Google Cloud) and tools like BigQuery, Vertex AI, and dbt.
Leadership experience in building, mentoring, and guiding high-performing data science teams.
Passion for applying data and AI to deliver meaningful business and patient outcomes.
Why join Eucalyptus?


Euc is also behind a growing family of digital healthcare clinics (Pilot, Kin, Software, Compound) across men‚Äôs health and well-being, fertility, skincare, and preventative health.

Here‚Äôs what makes joining Euc unique:

What‚Äôs next - Our goal for the next three years is to support 1 million patients globally to live better for longer. We‚Äôre launching into new conditions, demographics, and geographies as we build a truly preventive healthcare ecosystem.
Build something world-changing - We‚Äôre on the path to becoming the world‚Äôs largest international digital healthcare company. It will be challenging, fast-paced, and deeply rewarding.
Make real impact - You will deliver work that directly shapes patient outcomes and scales evidence-based care across markets.
Accelerate your growth - You will have high ownership, continuous feedback, and dedicated development support.
Join a motivated team - You will collaborate with talented peers to solve complex clinical and operational problems at scale.
What‚Äôs ahead in Australia?

Grow with us globally - Get mentorship from leaders across Australia, the UK, Germany, and Japan, collaborate with teams in the Philippines and South Africa, and explore new markets or travel internationally. Recognised on Hatch‚Äôs Hotlist as one of Australia‚Äôs top employers, we support early-career professionals to become future global leaders.
Shape your career - Access learning budgets, conferences, certifications, peer shadowing, and a global knowledge-sharing culture.
Be an owner - Equity for everyone means you share in our success.
Work where well-being matters - Experience catered wellness talks, exercise classes, whoops to track your wellbeing, free barista coffees, funded social clubs, and quarterly rooftop parties.
Innovate with purpose - Use state-of-the-art tools and contribute to bold, impactful solutions in healthcare.
Support at every stage - Benefit from parental and miscarriage leave, to health, professional development, and personal days, Whoop membership, and our Employee Assistance Program.

At Eucalyptus, we value individuals from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives, and we embrace the unique qualities each person brings. When you apply, please let us know of any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

Job Title: Reporting and Insights Analyst (3 Month Contact)
Ad Text:
About the Business

A major player in the financial services sector is engaging specialist capability to support a time-critical reporting workstream within a broader performance improvement program. The organisation operates in a highly regulated environment and places strong emphasis on analytical integrity, clarity of insight, and effective decision support.

This assignment is build-focused. You will be responsible for developing new dashboards and reporting solutions from scratch, rather than maintaining or enhancing existing reports. The role sits at the intersection of performance analysis, regulatory reporting, and stakeholder engagement, requiring both technical depth and strong commercial judgement.

What You‚Äôll Be Doing
Develop Power BI dashboards and reporting solutions that clearly articulate investment performance
Convert complex data and stakeholder requirements into structured, easy-to-use reporting outputs
Utilise existing datasets and models to produce reliable and scalable insights
Apply best-practice Power BI design principles to ensure clarity, usability, and consistency
Ensure reporting outputs align with governance frameworks and regulatory expectations
Work closely with performance, risk, and regulatory stakeholders to deliver agreed outcomes
Provide specialist reporting expertise to support the wider performance improvement initiative
What You‚Äôll Bring
Proven experience delivering Power BI reporting solutions end-to-end in a financial services setting
Strong exposure to investment performance or asset management reporting
Advanced Power BI capability, including DAX, data modelling, and dashboard design
Ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced, project-based contract environment
Clear communication skills and confidence engaging with senior stakeholders
If you would like to hear more, reach out to Luke Traynor at luke.traynor@troocoo.com

Senior Data Engineer

At Elula, we partner with some of Australia's top financial institutions to tackle a wide range of business challenges through cutting-edge AI-as-a-service (AIaaS). Our vision? To make the complex simple and easy, delivering amazing customer experiences and personalisation that matters.

Our products leverage machine learning, productionised models, data pipelines, explainable AI, and rich visualisations to drive customer engagement, retention and insights. We're constantly pushing the envelope, uncovering the ever-evolving needs of customers and staying ahead of the curve.

Join a team of some of the brightest minds in data science and engineering; experts with years of experience and a passion for delivering smarter decision-making. It's a fast-paced, high-performing and collaborative environment where creativity and learning take centre stage, and the work is as fun as it is rewarding.

Find out more about us at¬†https://elula.ai/team/.




The role

As a Senior Data Engineer at Elula, you will play a key role in building and maintaining the data that powers our AI-as-a-Service platform. You will be expected to operate autonomously, support and guide others. You will contribute expert knowledge to design, implement, and optimise data pipelines, models and tools, ensuring that our data is accurate, reliable, and scalable. You will collaborate closely with data scientists, software engineers, and customer-facing teams working end-to-end across the data lifecycle - from ingestion and modelling through to validation and delivery.

We're looking for someone who jumps at the opportunity to work autonomously on open-ended problems and thrives in an environment where collaboration, ambition, and excellence is paramount. Our ideal candidate is a stellar communicator, able to connect with all types of people, who puts their hand up, takes ownership, and is never afraid to ask for help when needed.

To be successful in this role, you will be expected to demonstrate the following skills and experience.
¬†

Technical and analytical competencies

Analyse, understand and interrogate complex data, assessing quality and fitment to design, build and maintain robust, scalable data pipelines.

Diagnose and resolve complex data quality and pipeline reliability issues, applying structured problem-solving and pragmatic remediation approaches.

Develop and optimise complex SQL logic across large datasets, with a strong focus on correctness, performance and maintainability.

Leverage Python to automate workflows, build and implement reusable tooling or libraries.

Apply data modelling principles in practice, designing data models that support analytical, operational and downstream use cases.

¬†

Ownership and decision-making

Own the delivery and ongoing reliability of data pipelines and integrations, working independently under general direction.

Exercise sound technical judgement when addressing complex issues, making informed trade-offs and escalating risks where appropriate.

Plan, prioritise and manage work effectively to meet agreed delivery timelines and quality expectations.

¬†

Technical leadership

Collaborate and influence across disciplines, working closely with engineers, analysts and data scientists to shape and deliver effective data solutions.

Support and enable junior engineers, providing guidance on technical approaches, tooling, and engineering best practices.

Communicate complex technical concepts clearly and confidently to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Continuously improve systems and practices, bringing curiosity, adaptability and a mindset of learning and refinement.

Adopt and share new tools, frameworks and techniques, contributing to the uplift of team capability and standards.




Preferred Skills and Experience

While the following are not required, they are highly valued.

Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Computer Science, or similar

Experience working in the financial services industry (e.g. banking, insurance or superannuation),

Familiarity with agile ways of working (sprints, huddles, retros, etc.)


Benefits

Elula‚Äôs people are at the core of all we do. Our benefits are just one way we show that.

Enjoy flexible working hours, and work from home two days per week, to better balance your personal and professional life.

Experience the freedom of working anywhere in Australia up to five days annually.

Give back to what matters to you with extra paid annual leave for volunteering.

Put your health first with an allowance for fitness and wellbeing.

Drive your development with financial support for approved training courses.

Level up with matched funding for career coaching.




Interested?

If you're excited about shaping the future of AI, this is where you belong! Submit your CV and cover letter telling us why you're the right fit for Elula and what makes you special!

We're committed to fostering a culture of inclusivity and equality. All are welcome to apply for our roles because we truly believe that diversity is a game changer.

Parramatta / Sydney
Temporary - Full-Time (35 HPW)
Clerk Grade 9/10, base salary ($129,464 - $142,665), plus employer's contribution to superannuation and annual leave loading

Your role

The successful candidate will assist with the implementation of change management plans to support a smooth transition within DCJ. The role requires engagement with internal and external stakeholders to support the delivery of the system and understand the impacts on people, processes, and technology. This is a hybrid role, working primarily from the Parramatta office (around 90% of your time) and occasionally from the Sydney office (about 10%), with flexibility to work from home as agreed. Your customer service skills are of a high standard as you will be meeting face-to-face with senior stakeholders within the Courts and Tribunals area.

The successful candidate will implement practical change plans that align with program objectives and client needs. You will provide timely advice and communication to relevant stakeholders across DCJ using a range of different communication channels.

You will also ‚Ä¶.

Work as part of the team of to act as the conduit between human users and technical systems, translating human needs, language, and behaviour into technical requirements.

What we're looking for

Support the implementation of integrated change management plans that focus on specific organisational needs of affected areas.
Develop and manage change deliverables including change readiness assessments, communications stakeholder engagement plans, training plans, and other change deliverables, as required.
Support and assist with aspects of the project and change implementation activities including research, qualitative and quantitative analysis, workshop facilitation process mapping and the development of communication collateral to support the change.
Tertiary qualifications in a related discipline and/or equivalent knowledge, skills and experience with demonstrated commitment to ongoing professional development.
Knowledge of, or experience working within, NSW Courts and Tribunals would be beneficial.

About the role
We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst to support the delivery of complex transformation and regulatory & compliance initiatives across our organisation. This role sits within the Transformation & Technology function and works closely with Product Owners, Delivery Leads and senior stakeholders to define, plan and deliver sustainable business outcomes.
¬†¬†
The Senior Business Analyst will lead analysis activities across large and high-risk initiatives, often operating in environments with regulatory, compliance and operational complexity. This role requires strong planning capability, confidence engaging at executive level, and the ability to work effectively across both Agile and Waterfall delivery models.
¬†¬†
Working as part of an inclusive and collaborative team your key responsibilities will include:
¬†¬†

Lead end-to-end business analysis activities across complex initiatives
Operate effectively within Agile and Waterfall delivery environments
Plan and manage scope, dependencies, risks and deliverables
Engage and influence senior and executive stakeholders, including clear and concise written communication
Translate regulatory and compliance requirements into practical business and system solutions
Define and document business requirements, user stories and process models
Lead and coordinate testing activities, including UAT planning and execution
Identify and implement process improvement and automation opportunities
Provide coaching and mentoring support to other Business Analysts within the team
Contribute to continuous improvement of business analysis standards, tools and ways of working
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
What will you bring?

Significant experience as a Business Analyst delivering complex initiatives
Strong experience working across Agile and Waterfall methodologies
Demonstrated strength in planning, organisation and delivery management
Proven executive-level stakeholder management capability
Experience working within banking regulated and compliance-driven environments
Solid experience with testing and quality assurance activities
Experience delivering process improvement or automation initiatives
High standard of written and verbal communication
Experience with CRM platforms such as Dynamics or Salesforce
Exposure to UX/UI concepts, including wireframing is desirable
IIBA or equivalent business analysis certification is desirable


¬†
What we can offer you
There‚Äôs life at work, and life outside of work ‚Äì and we understand that.
P&N Group is committed to creating a satisfying and fulfilling working environment, offering employee benefits and development opportunities that reward and help you perform to your potential and expand your experience and learning.

To help you live your best life through work, we offer an extensive range of employee benefits.

Work for a national multi-brand, customer-focused organisation
Enjoy flexible work arrangements
An incentive scheme for exceptional performance
Be supported with leadership and professional development
12 weeks paid parental leave for the primary care giver, and three weeks for the non-primary care giver
Generous discounts on home loans, personal loans, insurance and other banking products and services
Up to two weeks‚Äô additional purchased leave per year
Two days‚Äô paid volunteer leave each year to use with a community partner of your choice
An Employee Assistance Program
About us
P&N Group is amongst the largest customer-owned banking organisations in Australia, represented by P&N Bank in Western Australia and BCU Bank in New South Wales and southeast Queensland. Our purpose is to enrich the lives of our customers and their communities.
¬†¬†
With over $9 billion in assets and a head office in Perth and corporate offices in Coffs Harbour and Brisbane, we service over 200,000 customers across Australia from all walks of life supported by over 600 employees in group services, retail banking, broker, and business banking roles.
¬†¬†
We believe our culture is a real point of difference, and our values ‚Äì Focus on Members, Improve & Learn and Trust & Collaborate ‚Äì are fundamental to our ways of working. We offer a collaborative and inclusive workplace where our people feel a strong sense of belonging, are recognised, invested in, cared for, and are part of something bigger.
¬†¬†
What does our recruitment process look like?
The process can include a phone screen, virtual and/or face-to-face interview, psychometric testing, reference checks and all relevant background checks.
At P&N Group, we want to leverage the numerous benefits and innovative gains that a diverse workforce brings, and especially the high engagement that comes from a culture built on belonging and inclusion. We encourage people of all abilities, backgrounds, identities, ages and cultures to apply.

If you need assistance or require flexibility to be able to fully participate in the application process, please email us at recruitment@pnbank.com.au

The closing date for applications is 21 January 2026

We are looking for someone who can lead senior business programs from the front of the room. This role combines stage hosting, panel moderation, keynote delivery and research preparation. Event MCing

Manage transitions between keynote speakers, panels, firesides and breaks.

Panel Moderation

Moderate several panels per event with senior leaders across technology, operations, finance, risk, data or similar disciplines.

Prepare a discussion structure that pushes panellists beyond high level commentary.

Interrupt constructively, redirect when needed and draw out specific examples.

Keep panels focused, balanced and on schedule.

Lead conversations that reveal practical decisions, challenges and lessons.

Keynote Segments

Present confidently without relying on slides or dense decks.

Produce briefing notes for panellists and interviewees, including angles, likely tensions, and practical questions.

Pre Event Preparation

Identify contrasting views that can make discussions more dynamic and useful.

Contribute to the event run sheet and overall content flow.

On Camera and Media

Able to think on your feet, connect ideas live, and salvage weak answers without the audience noticing.

Who This Suits

Someone who enjoys leading rooms of senior professionals and is energised by live discussion.

Someone with a research or media background who can switch between preparation and delivery smoothly.

Someone who can balance authority and neutrality while keeping discussions sharp and practical.

Ad Text:

The Boeing MQ-28 - Ghost Bat is a globally significant program delivering disruptive advantage to support Defence operational capabilities. Essential skills & experience

Expertise designing large‚Äëscale data platforms: data lakes, data warehouses, streaming platforms, feature stores and analytical pipelines
